Tailwind CSS is the Utility Framework for CSS.

Following are the Usage of Tailwind CSS :

||Utility-First Fundamentals:

1) For Background-color we use ,

bg-colorname

2) For text color we use ,

text-colorname

3) For Size of the text we use ,

text-3xl

4) For Margin we use ,

m-4

5) For making the contents center we use ,

grid place content-center

6) For making the contents horizontal & vertical we use ,

h-screen , utility to make an element space that entire height of the veiwport.

7) For Padding we use ,
Note : We can also use by giving the axis name or location,
p-10
px-2
py-3
pt-3
pb-4

8) For Width we use ,

max-w-small
or
w-5

9) For Border Radius we use ,

rounded-3xl

10) For Shadow we use ,

shadow-lg

11) For Align-items we use ,

flex item-center

12) For Justify-contents we use ,

flex justify-center

13) For space between object we use ,

space-x-2

14) For height & width of the image size we use ,

h-12
w-12

15) For font size we use ,

font-bold

16) For Smaller Text we use ,

text-base

17) For Margin top we use ,

mt-4

18) For Maximum Width we use ,

max-w-sm

19) For Overflow of the image  we use ,

overflow-hidden

20) To Cover full image we use ,

object-cover

21) For Uppercase of the text we use ,

uppercase

22) For Spacing of the text we use ,

tracking-wider

23) For Padding the x axis and to give as a pixel sixe we use ,

px-[4px]

// Hover , Focus And Other States :

24) For Hover we use ,

hover : color name

25) When The window is in Dark mode we use,

dark : color name

It only runs only when the system is in dark mode otherwise it will not implement this property.


// Responsive design :

26) Using responsive utility variants to build adaptive user interfaces.
Tailwind uses a mobile-first breakpoint system.
Folowing are the breakpoints,

`sm` for small we use, sm: color of the text || place of the contens.
`md` for medium we use, sm: color of the text || place of the contens.
`lg` for large we use, sm: color of the text || place of the contens.
`xl` for x-large we use, sm: color of the text || place of the contens.
`2xl`for 2xl we use, sm: color of the text || place of the contens.

We can see this with the help of the example,
<div class="text-white sm:text-amber-500 lg:text-amber-200 my-5">
    <p>Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet consectetur adipisicing elit. Facere, commodi.</p>
</div>

In the above example,It sets the breakpoint to specific condition when it hits specific breakpoint it turns the color of the text.

27) For Hiding The Element we use,

hidden

28) For Cursor we use,

cursor-pointer

29) For Menu Bar we use,

&#8801

30) For Border we use,

border color name

31) For Border Bottom we use,

border-b-2

32) To Store Items one below another we use,

flex flex-col

33) To Wrap a Item in a new row instead of overflowing or shrinking too much we use,

flex flex-wrap

34) For Gap between elements we use,

gap-20

